mods:titleInfo.mods:title: A revision of the genera Acrosathe Irwin and Lyneborg, Arenigena Irwin and Lyneborg, and Litolinga Irwin and Lyneborg (Diptera: Therevidae: Therevinae) from the Nearctic Region

subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis. The male of
Acrosathe vanduzeei
is similar to
A. otiosa
in having the wing veins and cross-veins with a dark brown margin. It differs from
A. otiosa
in having the setae on male sternite 8 continuous across posterior margin ( Fig. 35 ); the AAP dorsal view ( Figs. 37–38 ) broadly rounded laterally, lateral view ( Fig. 38 ) short, extending to middle of distiphallus; and the ventral apodeme ( Fig. 37 ) broad, not reaching anterior margin of dorsal apodeme. The female of
A. vanduzeei
is similar to
A. falcata
in having the frons with a small dark brown pubescent area dorsolaterally ( Fig. 41 ) but is separated from
A. falcata
in having the furca oval ( Fig. 42 ) with the anterior and posterior margins rounded.

Head. Length 1.00–1.20, 1.14 mm . Ocellar tubercle dark reddish brown, pubescence gray, dense; setae dark reddish brown, elongate. Eyes holoptic, separated by distance 0.2 times width of median ocellus; ommatidia smaller ventrally and laterally. Frons pubescence white, dense, dark brown, glabrous on dorsal fourth; setae white to pale brownish gold (occasionally with scattered dark brown setae, MEI 113632 with dorsal patch of black setae), elongate on ventral three-fourths. Antenna dark brown, scape pubescence gray, dense; antenna/head length 0.7–0.8, 0.8; scape length 0.30–0.40, 0.37 mm , width 0.14–0.20, 0.18 mm , length/ width 1.7–2.4, 2.1, scape/pedicel length 3.0–4.3, 3.6, scape/flagellum width 0.9–1.4, 1.2, setae white to pale brownish gold, elongate; pedicel length 0.08–0.12, 0.10 mm , width 0.12–0.16, 0.14 mm , length/width 0.6–0.8, 0.7; flagellum length 0.32–0.48, 0.42 mm , width 0.13–0.15, 0.14 mm , length/width 2.1–3.4, 2.9, flagellum/scape length 0.9–1.4, 1.1. Parafacial pubescence white, dense; setae white to yellowish gold (occasionally dark brown). Maxillary palpus reddish brown; length 0.40–0.60, 0.51 mm , width 0.06–0.08, 0.08 mm , length/width 5.0–7.3, 6.6; setae white to brownish gold, elongate. Genal setae white to yellowish gold, elongate. Occipital setae white, elongate (occasionally becoming brownish gold dorsally or with scattered dark brown setae); macrosetae dark brown (yellow in many specimens or absent). Postocular macrosetae dark brown (yellow in many specimens, or occasionally a mixture of yellow and dark brown macrosetae).

Thorax. Macrosetae 3–4, 3 np, 1–2, 2 sa, 1 pa, 1–2, 1 dc. Mesonotum with vittae dull brown, separated by gray pubescence; setae white to brownish gold, elongate, subappressed intermixed with dark brown, erect setae. Postpronotal setae pale yellow to brownish gold, elongate. Prosternum setae white. Pleuron pubescence gray, dense; setae white to pale brownish gold, elongate on propleuron, anepisternum, katepisternum, laterotergite, metanepisternum, and scutellum. Wing. Membrane pale gray, veins and cross-veins brown with brown margin at fork of R 4+5 , r-m, apex of discal cell, apex of cell bm ; length 5.8–7.2, 6.4 mm , width 1.9–2.5, 2.2 mm , length/width 2.2–3.3, 2.8; cell m 3 open widely, closed at wing margin, or closed and petiolate. Halter brown. Legs. Coxal pubescence silver, dense; setae white, elongate; apical macrosetae dark reddish brown, hindcoxa with 1 posterolateral macroseta. Femora dark yellow, apex dark brown; ventral setae white (occasionally brownish gold), elongate, dorsal setae white, appressed. Tibiae dark yellow becoming darker on apical half. Tarsus 1 dark yellow becoming dark reddish brown on apical half; 2–5 dark reddish brown.

FEMALE. Similar to male except for following. Variation (n=10).

Head. Length 1.10–1.24, 1.15 mm . Setae on ocellar tubercle occasionally dark yellow to pale yellowish brown. Frons pubescence white, dense on ventral half, dorsal half dark brown, pubescence brownish gray. Specimens from Monterey County south to Orange County have a small area of brown pubescence dorsolaterally ( Fig. 41 ). Specimens from Santa Cruz north to Sonora County have narrow, dark brown, pubescent bar ( Fig. 40 ) mediolaterally, separated medially by yellowish brown pubescence (occasionally extending completely across frons as horizontal bar); setae white to pale yellow (occasionally with scattered dark brown setae), elongate ventrally and dark brown to brownish gold, subappressed dorsally. Antenna/head length 0.71–0.87, 0.80; scape length 0.36–0.42, 0.40 mm , width 0.16–0.22, 0.18 mm , length/width 1.9–2.5, 2.2, scape/pedicel length 3.0–5.0, 3.9, scape/flagellum width 1.1–1.4, 1.2, setae white, elongate intermixed with dark brown, elongate setae which grade into dark brown macrosetae; pedicel length 0.08–0.12, 0.10 mm , width 0.14–0.16, 0.15 mm , length/width 0.5–0.9, 0.7; flagellum length 0.36–0.50, 0.42 mm , width 0.14–0.16, 0.15 mm , length/width 2.4–3.3, 2.8, flagellum/scape length 0.9–1.2, 1.1. Maxillary palpus length 0.44–0.66, 0.57 mm , width 0.08–0.10, 0.11 mm , length/width 4.3–6.8, 5.2. Postocular macrosetae generally dark brown (occasionally mixed with dark yellow macrosetae or solely dark yellow macrosetae). Occipital macrosetae occasionally yellow.

Thorax. Macrosetae 3 np, 2 sa, 1 pa, 1–2, 1 dc. Mesonotum with vittae dark brown, separated by dense, gray pubescence. Wing. Length 6.7–7.5, 6.8 mm , width 1.8–2.5, 2.2 mm , length/width 2.7–3.4, 3.2. Halter brown.

Abdomen. Dark brown, pubescence gray, dense on posterior three-fourths of tergites 1–4 and most of tergites 5–8; dorsal setae white to pale yellow appressed.
Terminalia
(MEI 163550). Furca ( Fig. 42 ) oval, anterior margin bounded; length 0.47 mm , width 0.40 mm ; anterolateral projection short.

Distribution.
Acrosathe vanduzeei
is known from California ( Fig. 53 ).

Habitats and Phenology.
Acrosathe vanduzeei
has been hand-netted or collected in pan or Malaise traps in dry or moist washes and on dunes. One adult has been collected from the nest of
Bembix comata
[= americana
comata Parker
]. Holston (2005) described the community structure and habitat partitioning of
A. vanduzeei
(as
A. novella
). Adults have been collected from March through October and December.

Specimens examined. Type specimens.
The holotype male of
Thereva vanduzeei Cole
is labeled "San Francisco, Golden Gate Pk., VI-6-20, Cal." and is in the CAS (
Type No.
1490).
